commits.message:
Merge pull request #2179 from mbacchi/envfile

addendum to GUI-2869

Thanks, Matt

Add systemd units

This adds five systemd units that replace functionality that was
previously handled with a large rc script:

1.  eucaconsole.service, the main worker process

2.  eucaconsole-memcached.service, the local memcached daemon

    When eucaconsole.service runs it requests that this service
    run as well.  To disable this service for cases such as an
    administrator-controlled web server, run ``systemctl mask
    eucaconsole-memcached.service''.  When this service is not masked,
    stops and restarts from eucaconsole.service propagate to this
    service.

3.  eucaconsole-nginx.service, the local web server

    The notes from eucaconsole-memcached.service apply to this service
    as well.

4.  eucaconsole.keygen.service, the session key generator

    When eucaconsole.service runs it requests that this service run
    as well.  If this happens and /etc/eucaconsole/session-keys.ini
    is missing or empty, the eucaconsole-keygen script generates
    that file.

5.  eucaconsole-certgen.service, the TLS file generator

    When eucaconsole.service runs it requests that this service run
    as well.  If this happens and /etc/pki/tls/certs/eucaconsole.crt
    or /etc/pki/tls/private/eucaconsole.key is missing or empty,
    the eucaconsole-certgen script generates them.

``python setup.py install'' will not install these systemd-related
files by default.  To install them, use ``--init-system systemd''.

Make setup.py install config files

setup.py's data_files directive doesn't appear to have an easy way
of renaming files as they are installed, so in addition to installing
our configuration files to /etc/eucaconsole, this commit also renames
conf/console.default.ini in the source tree to conf/console.ini.
Note that the "launcher.sh" script uses a configuration file at the
top of the source tree, not the conf directory.
